      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ELEGANT EMBER (1) is a consistent dog overall, in the frame at four of 17 starts including eight wins but missed the frame latest when fifth (23.40) over 400m at this track. Rarely misses off this draw. Has the inside draw and looks tough to beat. DANYO'S ALBIE (8) struggled in tougher grade last start after losing his position early at Murray Bridge, but prior to that won by a nose at Murray Bridge Straight (16.81) beating Binnaway Pearl in a OPEN on April 1. Can do much better this time. WEBLEC SNIP (5) is mixing form lately, finishing out of the placings last time at this track but was a Other winner two back at this track. Can turn it around this time. FENCER MAX (2) was strongly fancied last time but finished second (19.88), beaten 4 lengths. Overdue and is among the main hopes.",
